textDisplay:
@nonchalantree6604  _Frozen II_ was made because the original _Frozen_ made so much money, not just at the box office, but mostly in merchandise sales and other ancillary markets.  It is one of the most lucrative, valuable franchises ever created, and Disney naturally wanted to keep it going strong.  The directors originally had no plans to make a sequel whatsoever, and instead looked forward to their next new project, but Disney management told them to try to come up with a good idea for a sequel.

To be fair to Disney (the parent company) and Disney Animation (Walt Disney's original studio, which actually made these movies), they weren't going to proceed until they had a good concept that everyone could get behind, and that took an additional two years or so.  It will answer (or attempt to answer) the main question fans have, which is the origin of Elsa's powers, and this works perfectly because Elsa herself would naturally want to know.

In short, Disney want to make even more money and many people want a movie like this--that is why _Frozen II_ was made.

